    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{3}{r-6}-\frac{6r}{r^{2}-36}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3}{r+6}, r\ne 6</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{3}{r-6}-\frac{6r}{r^{2}-36}} 
      \amp = {\frac{3}{r-6}}-\frac{6 r}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = \frac{3\cdot({r+6})}{({r-6})\cdot({r+6})} -\frac{6 r}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{3\mathopen{}\left(r+6\right)-6r}}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{3r+18-6r}}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-3r+18}}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-3\mathopen{}\left(r-6\right)}}{(r - 6)(r + 6)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3}{r+6}, r\ne 6}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{r-6}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {6}</m>.</p>
</solution>
